The paper focuses on designing a mobile robot system with a visual tracking algorithm to follow humans, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The use of Siamese networks and optical flow information in the visual tracking algorithm suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The unified controller for the mobile robot and pan-tilt camera suggests the involvement of control systems (cs.SY) techniques.
